# Tool Requirements and Installation

## Required Tools
The following tools are required for development and testing:

### Development Environment
- [Laragon](https://laragon.org/download/): Provides PHP, MySQL, and Apache/Nginx
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/): JavaScript runtime
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/): Node.js package manager
- [Composer](https://getcomposer.org/): PHP dependency manager

### Testing Tools
- [jq](https://stedolan.github.io/jq/): JSON processor
- [GitHub CLI](https://cli.github.com/): GitHub command-line interface

## Installation Methods
Tools can be installed in the following ways:

### Automatic Installation
The [setup-tools.ps1](mdc:.codespaces/testing/scripts/setup-tools.ps1) script handles automatic installation:
- Uses Chocolatey for package management
- Installs Laragon for PHP and Composer
- Configures environment variables
- Verifies installations

### Manual Installation
If automatic installation fails:
1. Install Laragon for PHP and Composer
2. Install Node.js and npm from official website
3. Install jq using Chocolatey or direct download
4. Install GitHub CLI using official installer

## Version Requirements
- PHP: 8.0 or higher
- Node.js: LTS version
- Composer: Latest version
- jq: Latest version
- GitHub CLI: Latest version

## Environment Variables
The following environment variables should be set:
- `PATH`: Include tool installation directories
- `GITHUB_TOKEN`: For GitHub API access
- `COMPOSER_HOME`: For Composer configuration
